parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine block plug can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the passenger's side of the engine block
caused by a faulty plug inserted by the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and blowout can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially result in rollover, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of air pressure
loud noise
vibration
and loss of control while driving
especially at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake rotors and pads can lead to a loss of braking effectiveness, increasing the stopping distance and risk of accidents.
symptoms: Grinding noise when applying the brakes
spongy brake pedal
vibrations when braking
reduced braking power
increased stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibrations when braking, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vibration or pulsation when applying the brakes
grinding noise when applying the brakes
spongy brake pedal
reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake pad wear sensors can lead to unexpected brake failure, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: No warning lights or notifications for worn brake pads
sudden loss of braking power
grinding noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the seat belt is a critical safety component designed to restrain occupants.
symptoms: The seat belt comes completely out of its retractor
the seat belt is loose or detached
the seat belt webbing is frayed or damaged
the seat belt buckle or latch is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the seat belt over time can cause it to fail in an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt webbing is cracked
frayed
or brittle
the seat belt is showing signs of wear or damage
the seat belt is not retracting properly
the seat belt is not functioning as intended.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the right axle and wheel can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also result in costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: The right wheel falls off or becomes loose while driving
the vehicle pulls to one side
unusual noises or vibrations come from the right wheel area
the vehicle becomes difficult to steer or handle.
